{{notability|date=November 2018}} {{Infobox NGO | name = The Live Love Laugh Foundation | logo = | type = Community Service | founded_date = 2015 | founder = [[Deepika Padukone]] | location = [[Bangalore]] | origins = | key_people = Anna Chandy <ref>{{cite News|url=http://businessworld.in/article/How-Deepika-Padukone-s-Foundation-TLLLF-Support-Mental-Wellness/10-10-2017-128157/|work=Business World|title=How Deepika Padukone’s Foundation TLLLF Support Mental Wellness|accessdate=22 March 2018|date=10 October 2017}}</ref>, Kiran Mazumdar Shaw, Dr. ShyamK. Bhat, Anirban Das Blah, Nina Nair <ref>{{cite news|url=https://scroll.in/bulletins/108/changing-the-conversation-around-mental-health-in-rural-india|work=scroll.in|title=Changing the conversation around mental health in rural India|accessdate=22 March 2018|date=27 November 2017}}</ref> | area_served = | focus = [[Mental health]] | method = | revenue = | endowment = | num_volunteers = | num_employees | num_members = | owner = | Non-profit_slogan = | homepage = http://www.thelivelovelaughfoundation.org }}
'''The Live Love Laugh Foundation''' is a [[Nonprofit organization|non-profit organisation]] that deals with [[mental health]] issues.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/lifestyle/health-and-wellbeing/150517/live-love-laugh-and-the-depressions-gone.html|title=Live, love, laugh, and the depression’s gone!|date=2017-05-15|work=Deccan Chronicle|access-date=2017-05-25|language=en}}</ref> It was founded in 2015 by [[Deepika Padukone]] as a [[Nonprofit organization|non-profit]] [[Non-governmental organization|NGO]] to bring awareness to [[mental health]] in India. In 2016, the organization launched a program called "You Are Not Alone".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/education/story/live-laugh-love-foundation/1/956101.html|title=TLLLF's You Are Not Alone programme covers 276 schools in six states : News|website=indiatoday.intoday.in|access-date=2017-05-25}}</ref> [[Facebook]] is working with the organization to prevent [[suicide|suicides]] from being livestreamed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://factordaily.com/facebook-live-suicide-artificial-intelligence-support/|title=What Facebook is doing to help those wanting to commit suicide, and what you can do|date=2017-04-26|work=FactorDaily|access-date=2017-05-25|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/live-love-laugh-foundation-deepika-padukone-launches-organisation-for-mental-health-issues-2381650.html|title=Live Love Laugh Foundation: Deepika Padukone launches org for mental health issues|date=2015-08-06|work=Firstpost|access-date=2017-05-25|language=en-US}}</ref>
==Mission==
The Foundation focuses on the following objectives:
* To create awareness and reduce the stigma around depression * To fund and support community-based mental health projects that can have a sustainable and a large-scale impact on the society. * To support research in the area of mental health in India.
